Since the tensor product is a right exact functor, this implies that localization by maps exact sequences of -modules to exact sequences of formula_4-modules. In other words, localization is an exact functor, and formula_4 is a flat -module.

This flatness and the fact that localization solves a universal property make that localization preserves many properties of modules and rings, and is compatible with solutions of other universal properties. For example, the natural map
